1
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,480
I shelved her

2
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,960
because I didn't think she'd be popular.

3
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:39,640
Nowadays, sweet singers
just don't sell anymore.

4
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,280
PREVIOUS EPISODE

5
00:02:41,360 --> 00:02:43,440
Let's be honest. How much are we talking?

6
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,440
Ten million.

7
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,960
Can you pay that?

8
00:02:47,040 --> 00:02:50,600
I also have videos of the conflicts
between you and Boss Noo.

9
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:54,440
And if these videos reach the police…

10
00:02:56,120 --> 00:02:58,400
I'm going to have you move
to Boss Nok's label.

11
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,680
If you want to date her, I won't stop you.

12
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:06,040
Just don't let the fans know yet.

13
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,680
You two still don't know yet?

14
00:03:10,240 --> 00:03:11,960
Puna is moving

15
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:14,200
to Boss Nok's label as a singer.

16
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:15,920
Puna.

17
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,960
-Whoa, wait.
-Puna!

18
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:25,280
Chaiya.

19
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,480
I'll wait outside.

20
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,360
Let me take your things.

21
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:02,120
What happened?

22
00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:09,120
Why did you leave the company?
Why didn't you tell me?

23
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,040
It's something the executives
were discussing.

24
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:18,000
I only just found out a moment ago,
like everyone else.

25
00:04:26,880 --> 00:04:27,960
Chaiya.

26
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:32,840
Since you're here,

27
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:36,080
you have to be very careful.

28
00:04:36,960 --> 00:04:40,040
Don't do anything reckless.
It's dangerous.

29
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,720
I'll remember what you said.

30
00:04:53,040 --> 00:04:54,560
If you need help…

31
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,320
just call me, okay?

32
00:05:02,760 --> 00:05:03,880
Thank you.

33
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,320
You can call me anytime.

34
00:05:16,520 --> 00:05:17,680
As for me,

35
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,000
I'll call you too.

36
00:05:22,960 --> 00:05:23,920
Sure.

37
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:42,920
Wait.

38
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:58,840
Take care of yourself.

39
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,960
You too.

40
00:06:20,240 --> 00:06:22,760
Don't just focus on keeping others safe.

41
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,760
You need to learn to take care
of yourself too, understand?

42
00:08:26,640 --> 00:08:27,840
Puna.

43
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:30,520
Are you okay?

44
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,960
I'm fine.

45
00:08:34,559 --> 00:08:36,919
You say you're fine,
so why are you crying?

46
00:08:38,840 --> 00:08:40,679
You don't want to leave, do you?

47
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:42,720
If that's the case, I can talk to Dad.

48
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:44,360
That's not it.

49
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:46,160
I'm really fine.

50
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,120
Are you sure?

51
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:53,640
Yes. I should get going now.

52
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,520
Wait, Puna.

53
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,400
Well then,

54
00:09:00,760 --> 00:09:01,720
let me give you a ride.

55
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,320
-But…
-Puna.

56
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:08,360
Let me do something for you one last time

57
00:09:08,440 --> 00:09:09,840
before you leave.

58
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,080
Okay.

59
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:19,160
Alright, I'll take you there. Come on.

60
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,920
Good luck, Puna.

61
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:51,280
I hope you become the singer
you've dreamed of.

62
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:16,600
Here, your less sweet green tea.

63
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:20,960
I'll scan to pay.

64
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:24,040
All done.

65
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,440
Okay.

66
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,520
The cappuccino is nice and frothy,

67
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:32,040
but is there any chance of us
getting lovey-dovey?

68
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,320
I'm off now, Uncle!

69
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:37,120
Who's her uncle?

70
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,240
Uncle!

71
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:42,240
Is the iced tea ready yet?
You're too busy flirting.

72
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:45,880
I'm not your uncle.

73
00:12:46,520 --> 00:12:49,760
What? I'm just repeating
what she called you.

74
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,560
Already complaining
after a bit of waiting?

75
00:12:51,640 --> 00:12:53,560
You're desperate for love or what?

76
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:58,160
You don't get it.
He's been desperate for ages!

77
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,360
-Really?
-Yeah.

78
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:01,400
Of course!

79
00:13:03,120 --> 00:13:05,680
Ever since Kwanta, my beloved wife,

80
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:08,160
left me 20 years ago,

81
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,360
I haven't had a single woman around

82
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:13,200
to lift my spirits, not a single soul.

83
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,320
Here's the deal.

84
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:19,840
If any of you find a young woman
to be Maria's new mother,

85
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:24,000
I'll give them free coffee for life.

86
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,200
-Wow!
-Wow!

87
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:28,320
Giving away free coffee for life?

88
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:30,400
You really mean it, Village Head?

89
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:32,120
When I say it,

90
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,560
I mean every single word!

91
00:13:34,640 --> 00:13:35,560
-Wow.
-He means it.

92
00:13:39,200 --> 00:13:40,320
You know,

93
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,240
this is gonna blow up the whole shop.

94
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:45,080
Say it again, Dad.

95
00:13:45,160 --> 00:13:47,120
Who's gonna find me a new mom?

96
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,320
No.

97
00:13:49,080 --> 00:13:51,200
I'm not looking for anyone, dear.

98
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,840
Go away!

99
00:13:53,920 --> 00:13:56,000
We're not selling today,
and the shop's closed.

100
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:57,960
Hey! How can you close?

101
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,080
My iced tea isn't ready yet!

102
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:02,560
Hey, I haven't even ordered anything yet.
Closing already?

103
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,080
Exactly! I don't want to sell today.
Get out, quickly!

104
00:14:05,160 --> 00:14:06,360
Go! Get out!

105
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:09,560
Hey, leave now. Anywhere, just go!

106
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,520
What? Where do you want me to go?

107
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:13,400
-Up to you!
-Huh?

108
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,960
Up to me? I'm staying here!

109
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:18,680
-Get out! The family needs to talk.
-Yes.

110
00:14:18,760 --> 00:14:19,760
-Leave!
-Go! Hurry, shoo!

111
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:21,320
-Come back tomorrow!
-Quick, go!

112
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:22,920
Shoo!

113
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,400
Dad, remember.

114
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:31,200
If you ever try to find me a new mom,

115
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,520
you'll regret it!

116
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:38,240
Yeah, I'm not looking.

117
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:46,800
But I'll forgive you for today,
just this once.

118
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,360
Because I have good news to share.

119
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:51,640
Yes!

120
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,480
Good news?

121
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:56,360
It's good news about the music label.

122
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:59,360
Dad, have you heard? Puna,

123
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,840
she's left us!

124
00:15:01,920 --> 00:15:05,200
Gone for good, never coming back.

125
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,160
Is Puna dead?

126
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:09,800
Ugh, Dad!

127
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,400
She's not dead.

128
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:15,120
She just left Darathong Music.

129
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:17,520
Left? Where did she go?

130
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,080
BAI TONG MUSIC

131
00:15:43,040 --> 00:15:45,040
Thank you so much for bringing me here.

132
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:47,040
Mr. Sonrak, are you feeling better?

133
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,920
I'm feeling better now.

134
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:52,720
But the thing that's still not okay…

135
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:54,840
What is it?

136
00:15:54,920 --> 00:15:57,800
I still haven't eaten anything delicious.

137
00:15:59,280 --> 00:16:02,320
Didn't you say
you'd cook for me at my place?

138
00:16:02,400 --> 00:16:03,400
Did you forget?

139
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:06,320
I didn't forget.

140
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:09,680
Just call me when you have time.

141
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:11,000
Sure.

142
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:15,160
Now that you're at the new company,
if you need anything,

143
00:16:15,240 --> 00:16:17,440
just message me. Don't hesitate.

144
00:16:18,360 --> 00:16:20,760
-Thank you so much.
-Yes.

145
00:16:22,280 --> 00:16:25,880
Teacher Mueangphrai,
I'll leave her in your care.

146
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:28,120
Don't worry.

147
00:16:28,200 --> 00:16:30,120
I'm already looking after her.

148
00:16:30,200 --> 00:16:31,880
Puna, remember.

149
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:35,280
I'll support you in everything.

150
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,080
Thank you.

151
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:59,840
I wonder what we'll face
after moving to the new label.

152
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:04,720
Yeah, I hope no one bullies us again.

153
00:17:08,280 --> 00:17:10,400
Hello, you two.

154
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:11,599
Hello.

155
00:17:11,680 --> 00:17:14,119
I'm sorry about the other day.

156
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:16,119
I may have hit a bit too hard.

157
00:17:17,800 --> 00:17:21,000
It's okay. I don't mind.

158
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:23,760
As for me, thinking back,

159
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,400
I'd like you to hit me again.

160
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:27,440
Just one more time.

161
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:28,840
Wanna go for it?

162
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,200
No! Stand your ground!

163
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:34,040
Anyway, nice to meet you.

164
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:36,160
I'm Puna, and this is…

165
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:37,560
Mueangphrai.

166
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:39,240
Mueangphrai.

167
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,360
And what are your names?

168
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:42,680
I'm Dam.

169
00:17:42,760 --> 00:17:45,320
Dark on the outside, but my heart's pure.

170
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:50,600
And I'm Dodden,
or you can just call me Den.

171
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:54,720
Let's go, Dam.

172
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:00,840
Hello.

173
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,280
I'm Emily.

174
00:18:03,360 --> 00:18:05,520
Boss Nok asked me to help
take care of the accommodations

175
00:18:05,600 --> 00:18:07,320
for you, Teacher Mueangphrai and Puna.

176
00:18:08,600 --> 00:18:10,120
We're staying here too?

177
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:12,200
Yes! This is a singing school

178
00:18:12,280 --> 00:18:13,960
with dorms upstairs.

179
00:18:14,040 --> 00:18:16,240
The system here
is kind of like in South Korea.

180
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:18,480
Whether it's eating, sleeping, or resting,

181
00:18:18,560 --> 00:18:20,720
it's like a boarding school,
like living at the label.

182
00:18:21,320 --> 00:18:22,480
Wow!

183
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,560
The label may be small,
but the system isn't small at all.

184
00:18:26,920 --> 00:18:29,760
By the way, where's Boss Nok?

185
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:32,600
I'd like to go thank him personally.

186
00:18:32,680 --> 00:18:34,120
He's unavailable today.

187
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,960
He's in a meeting in Bangkok.

188
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:38,320
Let's check out your rooms first.

189
00:18:38,400 --> 00:18:41,480
When he's back, I'll schedule
a time for you. Follow me.

190
00:18:50,080 --> 00:18:51,960
This will be your room, Puna.

191
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:54,280
That corner over there is the living area.

192
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:56,760
And that room is your bedroom.

193
00:18:56,840 --> 00:18:59,160
Teacher, your room is right next door.

194
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,400
It's so nice. The room's adorable!

195
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,920
Moving into the company
will be convenient too.

196
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:06,360
Everything will be much easier.

197
00:19:06,440 --> 00:19:09,160
This key is for your room, Puna.

198
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,920
And this one is for you.

199
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:14,200
If you need anything,
just call me anytime.

200
00:19:15,480 --> 00:19:16,680
-Thank you.
-You're welcome.

201
00:19:25,800 --> 00:19:28,280
Hello. You're almost off work, right?

202
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:32,120
When you're done, come out quickly.

203
00:19:32,200 --> 00:19:34,760
I'll wait at the usual spot,
so we can go home together.

204
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,560
Alright, see you.

205
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:48,040
Weerachai.

206
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,400
Hello. I found him.

207
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:57,920
Where is he?

208
00:19:59,520 --> 00:20:01,800
Good. Keep an eye on him.

209
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:02,880
I'll head over quickly.

210
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:06,040
We have to capture him today.

211
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:09,680
Who did you find?

212
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:12,080
Weerachai. Go!

213
00:20:39,160 --> 00:20:40,280
Where are you going?

214
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,600
Weerachai!

215
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:48,840
They're over there.

216
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,680
Where are you going?

217
00:20:51,240 --> 00:20:53,640
Hey! Don't go.

218
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,320
Just keep an eye from a distance.

219
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:00,840
Why aren't you answering?

220
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,920
Hey, run!

221
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,600
Quiet.

222
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:34,280
Manat, take him and hide first.

223
00:21:34,360 --> 00:21:35,560
Got it. Go.

224
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,440
Damn it! Follow him!

225
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:46,640
You bastard!

226
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,240
Go after him!

227
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,720
Where did he go?

228
00:22:05,480 --> 00:22:08,280
He's probably around here.
You two, find him!

229
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:12,640
Oh, hey.

230
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:15,320
Hey. Did you see Weerachai?

231
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,480
I did. He went that way.

232
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,680
Then what are you doing here?

233
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:22,400
I'm here to shop.

234
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,720
Are you sure you came to shop?

235
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:27,440
Where's your stuff?

236
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:31,360
Oh, I stopped to grab a bite first,
then I'll shop.

237
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:38,600
They're gone.

238
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,640
Hey, what are you afraid of?

239
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:46,680
I've helped you this much
and you still don't trust us?

240
00:22:53,600 --> 00:22:54,640
Fine.

241
00:22:56,080 --> 00:22:58,000
If you're taking me, lead the way.

242
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:18,760
What?

243
00:23:18,840 --> 00:23:21,760
The second floor of the laundry
is where they stash drugs?

244
00:23:23,200 --> 00:23:25,680
Yeah. The laundry delivery trucks

245
00:23:25,760 --> 00:23:27,960
distribute the drugs to customers.

246
00:23:29,720 --> 00:23:32,880
No wonder we couldn't catch them before.

247
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:33,880
Stop!

248
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:35,480
-Police!
-I'm not involved!

249
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:43,800
Captain.

250
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:46,760
Can I speak with you privately
for a moment?

251
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:49,000
Talk here if you need to.

252
00:23:50,400 --> 00:23:53,000
Better put on the handcuffs first.
They might resist.

253
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:23,240
No need to rush with the cuffs.
We'll take them off anyway.

254
00:24:23,760 --> 00:24:24,960
Don't tire yourself out.

255
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,480
Yes.

256
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:39,320
Don't do that, Captain.
Others might see and get suspicious.

257
00:24:41,080 --> 00:24:42,320
My apologies, sir.

258
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,880
It's all because of my ignorance.

259
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:50,720
I ended up obstructing
your operations in every way.

260
00:24:51,360 --> 00:24:52,560
I truly apologize.

261
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:54,600
It's alright.

262
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:57,280
Actually, I admire you, Captain Tom.

263
00:24:59,120 --> 00:25:00,600
While working,

264
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:03,600
I've gathered a lot of information
I'd like to share with you,

265
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:06,400
including what I just got from Weerachai.

266
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:08,680
Good.

267
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:19,640
Corporal Chom.

268
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:23,800
Release Mr. Chaiya and Mr. Manat.
It was all a misunderstanding.

269
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,560
Then we'll take our leave.

270
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,720
Go ahead.

271
00:25:38,600 --> 00:25:42,040
What's going on, Captain?
Why did you release them?

272
00:25:42,120 --> 00:25:44,840
And just now, I saw you salute Mr. Chaiya.

273
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,800
Doesn't this mean…

274
00:25:47,360 --> 00:25:48,280
Don't mention it, Corporal Chom.

275
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:50,200
And don't share this with anyone.

276
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:52,960
Everything here is confidential.

277
00:25:53,800 --> 00:25:54,760
Yes, Captain.

278
00:26:10,320 --> 00:26:13,720
You told Captain Tom the truth,
but I still feel worried.

279
00:26:15,720 --> 00:26:16,880
Worried about what?

280
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:22,200
I'm afraid this might reach

281
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,400
Superintendent Samuejai.

282
00:26:26,360 --> 00:26:27,280
No.

283
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:30,320
I trust Captain Tom won't say anything.

284
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:39,520
What about the dry cleaning place?
Have you told him?

285
00:26:41,440 --> 00:26:42,480
Yes, I've told him.

286
00:26:43,280 --> 00:26:45,680
I think he'll handle it somehow.

287
00:26:46,480 --> 00:26:49,720
I hope we weren't wrong about Captain Tom.

288
00:27:01,520 --> 00:27:03,600
DARATHONG MUSIC

289
00:27:05,600 --> 00:27:06,640
Chaiya.

290
00:27:06,720 --> 00:27:08,480
Yes, Ice? What's up?

291
00:27:08,560 --> 00:27:09,680
Here.

292
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:19,280
This is Puna's locket!

293
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:23,240
Yes. I found it in the costume room.

294
00:27:23,320 --> 00:27:25,520
But I didn't know how to return it to her.

295
00:27:25,600 --> 00:27:27,720
Could you give it back to her?

296
00:27:29,520 --> 00:27:30,600
Of course.

297
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:36,840
Ice, is my new outfit ready yet?

298
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:39,600
I'll go check on it.

299
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:41,400
-Go on.
-Right now!

300
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,120
Yes.

301
00:28:11,080 --> 00:28:12,920
Would this one be better, Miss Maria?

302
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:17,200
Hey, what's with you?

303
00:28:17,880 --> 00:28:19,880
My makeup, my hair,

304
00:28:19,960 --> 00:28:22,760
and my outfit,
none of this matches my taste.

305
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:24,960
Try paying attention
when you pick something!

306
00:28:25,040 --> 00:28:27,120
I'm sorry, Miss Maria.

307
00:28:27,200 --> 00:28:29,640
I'm really not good at this.
I tried my best.

308
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:32,720
Tried your best? Tried what?

309
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,720
The blouse is wrinkled,
and the skirt's crooked.

310
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:38,200
Come on. Put some effort into it.

311
00:28:38,280 --> 00:28:40,880
-Even an intern could do better.
-True!

312
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:45,680
What's going on?
It's loud enough to hear outside.

313
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,560
Mr. Sonrak.

314
00:28:48,640 --> 00:28:52,360
Look at Ice. She's clumsy
and can't get anything right.

315
00:28:53,520 --> 00:28:55,240
But this isn't really my job.

316
00:28:55,320 --> 00:28:58,360
I'm just helping until we find
a new staff member.

317
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:01,040
Even if you're just helping,

318
00:29:01,120 --> 00:29:02,800
do it properly!

319
00:29:02,880 --> 00:29:04,800
Sloppy work like this won't do.

320
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:07,200
-True.
-Calm down.

321
00:29:07,280 --> 00:29:09,520
Ice is Kamnan Pong's secretary.

322
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,560
She's helping out,
which is already kind of her.

323
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:17,240
Joey and Sophie, what are you two doing?

324
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:21,000
We're in charge of managing
the artists' schedule.

325
00:29:21,080 --> 00:29:22,200
That's great.

326
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,560
Then from now on,
you can help cover for Puna as well.

327
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:26,840
Mr. Sonrak.

328
00:29:26,920 --> 00:29:28,920
This is beyond our duties.
It's more than our pay!

329
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,880
Beyond your duties and pay?
Then maybe you should quit.

330
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:34,000
-Fine.
-Yeah.

331
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:36,640
-We'll cover for Puna ourselves.
-We'll do our best.

332
00:29:37,960 --> 00:29:40,200
That solves the problem.

333
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:43,760
Maria can relax knowing
someone reliable is handling it.

334
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:45,320
-Yes.
-And Ice,

335
00:29:45,400 --> 00:29:46,720
you can go back to your original duties.

336
00:29:47,680 --> 00:29:49,520
Thank you so much, Mr. Sonrak.

337
00:29:55,560 --> 00:29:57,720
-Can you do it?
-Yes.

338
00:29:57,800 --> 00:29:59,240
I'll take care of it.

339
00:30:00,520 --> 00:30:03,640
Such a tattletale! Tells on everything!

340
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:05,680
Are you talking about me?

341
00:30:05,760 --> 00:30:08,520
No, I mean Ice.

342
00:30:09,040 --> 00:30:11,480
-Fine then.
-She can't do anything.

343
00:30:11,560 --> 00:30:13,320
Makes us do everything for her.

344
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:15,800
Are you talking about me?

345
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:19,120
No, I'm talking about Ice.

346
00:30:20,640 --> 00:30:23,200
She has a Thai name too,
but she just goes by her English one.

347
00:30:23,280 --> 00:30:24,320
Hey!

348
00:30:24,400 --> 00:30:26,880
I went from Malee to Maria.

349
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,200
Who's got a problem with that?

350
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:29,920
No.

351
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:33,440
Ice, her old Thai name was Aye,

352
00:30:33,520 --> 00:30:35,760
but now it's Ice in English.

353
00:30:37,400 --> 00:30:39,160
-I think--
-Shut up!

354
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:48,200
TOP COUNTRY HITS

355
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,520
Let's have someone
help move this a bit more.

356
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,240
Sure. Just a moment.

357
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:56,160
Thank you.

358
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:07,240
Hello.

359
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,160
Nice to see you again.

360
00:31:09,760 --> 00:31:11,440
I'm so glad you remember me, Maria.

361
00:31:11,520 --> 00:31:13,360
Of course I remember.

362
00:31:13,440 --> 00:31:17,000
Just the other day, you interviewed me
on <i>Top Country Hits</i>.

363
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,960
Actually, this is a new show.

364
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:24,640
I'm the producer and in charge
of production as well.

365
00:31:24,720 --> 00:31:27,280
You manage both on-camera
and behind-the-scenes?

366
00:31:28,040 --> 00:31:29,840
Please don't get bored with my questions.

367
00:31:30,440 --> 00:31:31,520
No, I won't.

368
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,640
Are you ready? Shall we start filming?

369
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:35,320
Yes, I'm ready.

370
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,240
Take some behind-the-scenes shots too.

371
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:41,280
Huh?

372
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,840
Why me?

373
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:48,920
Mr. Singha asked the assistants
who came along

374
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:50,320
to take behind-the-scenes shots for PR,

375
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:52,200
but I can't take photos.

376
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:56,320
I can, but I'm worried it won't look good.

377
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:58,320
You're perfect for this.

378
00:31:58,400 --> 00:32:00,240
Just shoot. Stop complaining.

379
00:32:02,160 --> 00:32:03,120
Got it.

380
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:06,800
For the new song I'm working on,

381
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:09,120
I've given some ideas to the songwriter.

382
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,440
It's a song about love.

383
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:15,280
So your love right now

384
00:32:15,880 --> 00:32:20,480
is so full, it has to be expressed
in a song?

385
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,040
I'm not sure.

386
00:32:24,120 --> 00:32:28,040
I think it's better
to just let it happen naturally.

387
00:32:52,840 --> 00:32:54,400
Next cue, singing scene.

388
00:32:56,800 --> 00:32:59,120
Maria needs to change outfits, right?

389
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:02,640
-Yes. Maria, change into the new outfit.
-Okay.

390
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:05,960
Should we try it on with the set,
so the lighting can be adjusted?

391
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:07,920
Sure.

392
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,600
Sophie, bring the outfit here.

393
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:12,520
-Yes, Miss Maria.
-Got it.

394
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:18,800
Maria, I didn't bring
the performance outfit.

395
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:21,200
Can we use the same outfit, Director?

396
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,360
No, that's not allowed.

397
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:27,560
The outfit for the singing performance
and the interview must be different.

398
00:33:27,640 --> 00:33:29,280
We promised the client that.

399
00:33:29,360 --> 00:33:32,000
But we really didn't bring the outfit.

400
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:37,400
The show staff called to confirm
with Maria's team.

401
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,280
Someone named Sophie answered,
and I was listening in.

402
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:43,760
That was me.

403
00:33:43,840 --> 00:33:45,680
I really forgot.

404
00:33:46,520 --> 00:33:49,680
Does the show have a backup outfit?

405
00:33:49,760 --> 00:33:50,760
No.

406
00:33:50,840 --> 00:33:52,960
If we're not told in advance,
we don't prepare one.

407
00:33:57,200 --> 00:33:58,480
Maria.

408
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:02,360
Without the outfit,
I'll have to cut the singing segment.

409
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,240
The interview

410
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:07,480
won't air either.

411
00:34:07,560 --> 00:34:09,920
We'll need to postpone it.

412
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:15,080
Then I can't promote the song at all?

413
00:34:15,760 --> 00:34:17,120
I'm really sorry.

414
00:34:17,199 --> 00:34:20,520
The client is strict about this.
It's necessary.

415
00:34:24,040 --> 00:34:25,159
Let's go.

416
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,800
How does this team even work?

417
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:33,360
If the company finds out,
you two are done for.

418
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:35,440
Well…

419
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:38,679
Who could have known
the show would be this picky?

420
00:34:39,320 --> 00:34:42,320
Yeah, we weren't born
to do clothes anyway.

421
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:45,800
No one's perfect from birth.

422
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:47,360
Just so you know,

423
00:34:48,280 --> 00:34:50,520
you two can't measure up to Puna.

424
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:58,160
Everything's always compared to Puna.

425
00:34:58,240 --> 00:35:01,440
If she's so good,
why not let her handle your outfits?

426
00:35:03,880 --> 00:35:06,080
-Let's go grab something to eat.
-Geez!

427
00:35:15,040 --> 00:35:16,280
Wow!

428
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:20,200
You've made it.

429
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:24,000
We warmly welcome both of you

430
00:35:24,760 --> 00:35:28,400
to Bai Tong Music.

431
00:35:30,400 --> 00:35:33,640
I was just thinking of a song
to showcase Puna,

432
00:35:33,720 --> 00:35:36,680
but I can't decide on a style.

433
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,360
How about this?

434
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:42,160
Puna, could you sing me a song live?

435
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:43,960
Which song should I sing?

436
00:35:44,040 --> 00:35:46,200
The one you used
in the competition is fine.

437
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:49,040
-"Waiting for Him to Forget," right?
-Yeah, that works.

438
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:51,440
Go ahead, Puna. Give it your all.

439
00:35:55,360 --> 00:36:00,800
<i>I've waited. Waited so long…</i>

440
00:36:00,880 --> 00:36:03,280
-Dam, did you hear that?
-What?

441
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:06,920
<i>My heart unwavering and full…</i>

442
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:10,000
Of course I did. I'm not deaf.

443
00:36:10,080 --> 00:36:12,960
That voice again. it's amazing!

444
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:16,800
<i>Forgotten me, with no certainty at all</i>

445
00:36:16,880 --> 00:36:19,840
<i>I wait for him</i>

446
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:23,560
<i>But he forgets I'm waiting…</i>

447
00:36:23,640 --> 00:36:25,120
What are you doing, man?

448
00:36:25,200 --> 00:36:27,440
I know what you're thinking.

449
00:36:27,520 --> 00:36:29,400
She's our boss's new singer.

450
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:31,200
Yeah, I know already.

451
00:36:31,280 --> 00:36:34,280
<i>Waiting and pleading</i>

452
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:40,000
<i>With this lonely heart</i>

453
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:45,960
That's really good! Perfect!

454
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,040
Oh my goodness.

455
00:36:47,120 --> 00:36:48,000
Wow!

456
00:36:48,920 --> 00:36:52,160
It sounds amazing! But…

457
00:36:54,080 --> 00:36:55,800
It still doesn't work.

458
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,520
Right, Tu?

459
00:36:57,600 --> 00:36:59,840
Yes, Boss. I think it's not quite right.

460
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:04,800
For Puna, it should be
more dancey, upbeat,

461
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:07,640
flashy, sparkling, dazzling.

462
00:37:07,720 --> 00:37:09,040
That would suit her better.

463
00:37:09,120 --> 00:37:11,160
Like a parade float style?

464
00:37:12,280 --> 00:37:13,640
Exactly that, Teacher!

465
00:37:14,640 --> 00:37:16,960
That's trendy right now.

466
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:18,480
Guaranteed good revenue.

467
00:37:18,560 --> 00:37:21,360
If the views hit,
the earnings will skyrocket.

468
00:37:21,440 --> 00:37:23,720
Work comes easy,
TV, fairs, events, big productions.

469
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,120
Tons of work!

470
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:28,720
Done! Decision made.

471
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:31,000
Puna.

472
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:34,200
You aren't suitable for a dance song.

473
00:37:38,680 --> 00:37:39,800
-Not suitable.
-Not suitable.

474
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:41,800
Your song style

475
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:44,360
has to evoke imagination.

476
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:45,280
Wow, imagination?

477
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:46,680
An emotional song.

478
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:50,960
It should be sweet but bitter.

479
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:53,880
-Can't swallow, can't spit out.
-Sleepless nights.

480
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:56,080
-You want to love but can't.
-Oh no!

481
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:58,160
-You want to die but can't.
-Oh my God!

482
00:37:58,240 --> 00:38:00,320
You want to quit but can't.
Something like that.

483
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:05,400
Or simply, we need lyrics that cut deep.

484
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,760
So when Puna sings, people cry.

485
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:10,480
Trust me!

486
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:15,720
The audience will feel every note.

487
00:38:18,760 --> 00:38:20,880
Go find a songwriter who can do this, Tu!

488
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:23,840
That's a tough challenge.

489
00:38:23,920 --> 00:38:26,320
-Complaining again?
-Why don't you write it yourself?

490
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:28,600
Boss, it's just so hard to find someone

491
00:38:28,680 --> 00:38:30,640
who can do this style. It's hard!

492
00:38:30,720 --> 00:38:33,840
Hard doesn't mean impossible.

493
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:38,360
Or…

494
00:38:39,320 --> 00:38:41,200
should we have
Teacher Mueangphrai write it?

495
00:38:41,800 --> 00:38:45,000
-Teacher? Can you do it?
-Scatterbrained.

496
00:38:45,080 --> 00:38:46,240
Yes.

497
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,360
Once it's ready, I'll present it.

498
00:38:48,440 --> 00:38:50,520
Make it go bang, bang, bang!

499
00:38:50,600 --> 00:38:51,640
Whoa!

500
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,320
You mean to make it blow up!

501
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:55,920
I want this song

502
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:59,440
to make Puna blow up, bang, bang, bang!

503
00:38:59,520 --> 00:39:01,600
Let Singha regret underestimating us!

504
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,800
About the song, don't worry Puna.

505
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,400
Okay, I trust you, Teacher.

506
00:39:17,200 --> 00:39:21,360
I might look
for some old songs I've written

507
00:39:21,440 --> 00:39:23,040
and play them for the boss.

508
00:39:24,240 --> 00:39:27,440
That's great. I can try
singing them first,

509
00:39:27,520 --> 00:39:29,880
so I can show Boss Nok.

510
00:39:31,200 --> 00:39:33,400
I'll search at home first

511
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:35,400
and bring them for you to practice.

512
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,120
Okay.

513
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:57,240
They regularly pick up
and deliver laundry.

514
00:39:57,320 --> 00:39:58,640
Nothing seems suspicious,

515
00:39:59,240 --> 00:40:01,800
but the strange thing is Hao lives alone.

516
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:04,680
Where does he get the clothes
to wash every single day?

517
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:06,800
We will go check.

518
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:10,440
If we find any contraband,
we'll signal you.

519
00:40:10,520 --> 00:40:13,040
-Understood.
-And if they pass out,

520
00:40:14,200 --> 00:40:15,600
call an ambulance, okay?

521
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:54,280
Oh! Sorry.

522
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:56,400
Watch where you go! The path's wide.

523
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:57,800
Are you blind or what?

524
00:40:58,360 --> 00:41:00,760
I was in a hurry,
so I didn't watch my step.

525
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:02,880
Sorry again.

526
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,280
Are you hurt anywhere?

527
00:41:04,360 --> 00:41:06,720
Hey! What are you doing? Don't touch me!

528
00:41:08,040 --> 00:41:09,920
-I just want to check your health.
-Hey, stop!

529
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:14,320
Why are you arresting me, Officer?

530
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:17,040
You're under arrest
for possession of illegal drugs.

531
00:41:17,120 --> 00:41:19,720
-Take him away.
-Discuss the rest at the station.

532
00:41:19,800 --> 00:41:20,680
Move.

533
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:26,640
Just as the informant said,

534
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,600
the laundry shop is hiding drugs.

535
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:32,080
This is just a small-time customer.

536
00:41:32,840 --> 00:41:35,440
To get to the root, we'll have to raid

537
00:41:36,320 --> 00:41:39,240
the second floor of the laundry shop.

538
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:51,120
I don't know how that bag of drugs
ended up in the laundry.

539
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:53,080
Maybe those guys planted them.

540
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:55,400
Nobody planted anything.

541
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:58,600
Don't accuse the police.
Take him to the cell.

542
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:01,520
Move. Get up.

543
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:04,280
Get up.

544
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:15,520
-Hey! How did you get caught?
-Sergeant Biew.

545
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,280
They found out about the laundry shop.

546
00:42:18,880 --> 00:42:19,960
There's an informant reporting on it.

547
00:42:20,600 --> 00:42:21,720
We're screwed.

548
00:42:28,840 --> 00:42:30,120
He's here.

549
00:42:30,200 --> 00:42:32,920
You guys scheduled a meeting.
What's the business this time?

550
00:42:33,520 --> 00:42:34,480
Nothing much.

551
00:42:35,520 --> 00:42:36,640
Just wanted some extra info.

552
00:42:41,880 --> 00:42:43,280
You guys are really cops, right?

553
00:42:45,280 --> 00:42:46,360
We're just informants.

554
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:49,520
Are you sure? You're not lying?

555
00:42:50,760 --> 00:42:53,600
If we were lying,
we wouldn't be standing here.

556
00:42:53,680 --> 00:42:56,600
You saw the other day when we got caught.

557
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,160
That's reassuring.

558
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:04,200
My girlfriend, Aew,

559
00:43:04,280 --> 00:43:06,520
says the shop was ordered
to move the goods.

560
00:43:09,840 --> 00:43:12,640
-So the info leaked.
-Seems like it.

561
00:43:12,720 --> 00:43:14,760
Captain Tom is about to raid
with the police.

562
00:43:15,480 --> 00:43:16,680
We need to warn them,

563
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:17,840
or it'll be a foul.

564
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:29,560
What should we do, Captain?
Shall we raid now?

565
00:43:30,160 --> 00:43:31,200
Go!

566
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:35,920
-Yes?
-Captain.

567
00:43:36,960 --> 00:43:38,080
The goods aren't in the shop.

568
00:43:39,160 --> 00:43:41,120
Try following the guy named Tia.

569
00:43:41,200 --> 00:43:42,400
He's about to move the goods.

570
00:43:44,080 --> 00:43:45,080
Okay, understood.

571
00:43:50,840 --> 00:43:52,640
Have you delivered all the clothes yet?

572
00:43:53,480 --> 00:43:54,600
Still one left, Tia.

573
00:43:54,680 --> 00:43:56,080
Hurry up.

574
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:58,080
I'm taking the broken washing machine
for repair.

575
00:43:59,160 --> 00:44:00,280
Got it, Tia.

576
00:44:06,200 --> 00:44:07,800
-Follow him.
-Yes, sir.

577
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,440
There's a mole in our group.

578
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:21,240
We need to find him.

579
00:44:27,720 --> 00:44:28,880
Have the goods been moved yet?

580
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:31,320
About 90% done.

581
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:43,360
Yeah, I'll take care of it.

582
00:44:46,440 --> 00:44:48,480
Tia just called.

583
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:50,720
He said our truck is being followed.

584
00:44:52,040 --> 00:44:52,920
By who?

585
00:44:53,520 --> 00:44:55,400
Captain Tom.

586
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:58,720
Captain Tom.

587
00:45:02,720 --> 00:45:04,240
-Chit.
-Yes.

588
00:45:05,320 --> 00:45:07,880
Go help Tia, and if you get the chance,

589
00:45:07,960 --> 00:45:09,680
take out Captain Tom.

590
00:45:09,760 --> 00:45:10,720
Got it, Boss.

591
00:45:24,360 --> 00:45:26,080
Hey! What's going on?

592
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,120
Whoa!

593
00:45:30,280 --> 00:45:32,600
-What's wrong with the van?
-I'll check.

594
00:45:38,520 --> 00:45:40,520
Hey, Wong, take down the license plate.

595
00:45:41,040 --> 00:45:43,240
-Got it.
-Hey, Chit.

596
00:45:43,320 --> 00:45:45,320
-Where are you going?
-Got work.

597
00:45:48,120 --> 00:45:49,600
You two, follow them too.

598
00:45:49,680 --> 00:45:51,400
What kind of work, sir?

599
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:54,040
Cleanup duty.

600
00:45:55,120 --> 00:45:57,280
The car's in bad shape.
It might need a garage.

601
00:45:57,360 --> 00:45:59,200
Follow them first.

602
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:00,840
We'll deal with the car later.

603
00:46:03,360 --> 00:46:06,520
I want you to take out Captain Tom,
understand?

604
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:09,800
Go, quickly!

605
00:46:10,640 --> 00:46:12,640
-Move!
-Yes, sir.

606
00:46:28,920 --> 00:46:30,360
Call central police now.

607
00:46:30,440 --> 00:46:31,480
Get backup here.

608
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:34,520
The local cops aren't going to help us.

609
00:46:58,040 --> 00:46:59,040
Move!

610
00:47:06,480 --> 00:47:07,440
Hey, grenade! Take cover!

611
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,240
Captain, are you okay?

612
00:47:19,320 --> 00:47:21,520
I'm fine. Keep going!

613
00:47:46,680 --> 00:47:49,240
What do we do?
Captain Tom's at a disadvantage.

614
00:48:02,360 --> 00:48:03,400
Sergeant!

615
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:12,120
Hey!

616
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:13,240
What the hell are you doing?!

617
00:48:14,520 --> 00:48:16,240
Whoa! Chit, don't shoot! Don't!

618
00:48:16,960 --> 00:48:19,200
Damn it! Why'd you get in the way?

619
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:26,920
Someone like her
is perfect for that kind of job.

620
00:48:27,000 --> 00:48:30,040
Even after switching companies,
still stuck with the hard labor.

621
00:48:30,640 --> 00:48:32,960
I didn't expect
to see you here, Mr. Sonrak.

622
00:48:33,040 --> 00:48:33,880
I come over

623
00:48:33,960 --> 00:48:36,800
to Puna's place pretty often.

624
00:48:36,880 --> 00:48:39,320
-Hey!
-What's going on?

625
00:48:39,400 --> 00:48:40,720
NEXT EPISODE

626
00:48:41,320 --> 00:48:44,160
Today you're going to watch your friend

627
00:48:44,840 --> 00:48:46,160
die right in front of you!

628
00:48:48,400 --> 00:48:49,320
What are you gonna do?

629
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:50,880
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
